Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of Agent-Based Modeling and Simulation (ABMS) for modeling and simulating self-organization in wireless networks, particularly MANETs. This topic falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also mentions the use of self-organizing algorithms, which is a topic related to complex systems (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a platform for modeling and simulation, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
